  5. Income tax expense 

  The tax charge of GBP1.4m for the half year to 30 June 2017 reflects the anticipated effective tax rate of 35.3% for the year ending 31 December 2017.  Non-underlying items have been taxed using the relevant tax rates.  The effective tax rate is higher than the current UK tax rate of 20.0% due to the level of Group profits in the US which has an effective tax rate of 38.0%. The effective tax rate credit for the period ended 30 June 2016 was 33.8% and for the year ended 31 December 2015 was 24.9%. 

